{
  "texts": [
    "It turns out that the only non-trivial examples (i.e.",
    "not Einstein or locally homogeneous) have dim B = dim N = 2; see [Lot10,Prop.",
    "4.80].In order to do this, we use an explicit description of SL 2 (R)-Higgs bundles due to Hitchin [Hit87].",
    "Fix a Riemann surface Σ = (B 2, c) with χ(B 2) < 0 and let (L, β, γ) be an SL 2 (R)-Higgs bundle (cf.",
    "Example 4.6)."
  ]
}